javelin.model.world.location.fortification

Class Trove

  • java.lang.Object
    • javelin.model.world.Actor
      • javelin.model.world.location.Location
        • javelin.model.world.location.fortification.Fortification
          • javelin.model.world.location.fortification.Trove
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Trove
extends Fortification
    Represents all the resource types found in the game: gold, experience, keys, labor and rubies. Usually only 2 are offered per instance though, to increase randomization. Since the actual fight gives no xp or gold these results are doubled as treasure. TODO experience was a nice reward but too explotiable. You could dismiss mercenaries and have a larger XP reward, or divide the squad and have only reiceve all XP, which is super explotaible. If could trigger reward(Reward) just after the battle is over, this could be easily solved.

    alex
